{
  "stem": "27770.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And later on, once in a while, it was in a family, some wedding or bar mitzvah or some holiday or some special occasion or some rabbi came from another town, so we were invited to the other shul.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But most of the time, ours was with my father in the little shul, in my home town, where I used to live in the same street, in the same street was the shul.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was a rabbi.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But if you ask me what was his name, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To be honest, I was too young to understand the real antisemitism.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But once the start of the war, and the Hungarians occupied, roughly 1938, our hometown, we started to feel the antisemitism, day after day, more and more.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "First of all, they looked for all those Jews who didn't have citizenship.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They came from other countries, mostly from Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were taken away, already, started in 1941, 1942.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Slowly, they took them away.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Of course, we Jews, we thought only they mean the Polish people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We was never thinking that it would come the time they will take us, too.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this was the plan.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It went from one country to another country.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They took all the Jews away to concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "During the Hungarian time, the Hungarians-- let me point it out-- they were bigger antisemites than even the Germans.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Any problem, what they could do for the Jews, they were first there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "First, they started to make laws.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "In only certain schools could go Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I went to the Hebrew gymnasium, so I didn't have this problem.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But then later on, they took away, from Jewish people, the right to have stores.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And more and more Jewish people lost their stores.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They couldn't make a living.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
